1
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:53,500
[BEAR] There are
two kinds of worlds...

2
00:01:53,583 --> 00:01:55,500
Those that die
out on their own...

3
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:57,583
and those that are destroyed.

4
00:01:59,041 --> 00:02:00,041
[MORTE] Wow, you're
really trying to look

5
00:02:00,125 --> 00:02:01,416
cool up there, aren'tcha?

6
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:03,833
You know you're
just a bear, right?

7
00:02:03,916 --> 00:02:07,208
[BEAR] I'm a hero and I won't
dignify that with an answer.

8
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:10,125
So have either of you
figured out a plan yet?

9
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:13,291
We've just been drifting here
ever since our fuel ran out.

10
00:02:13,375 --> 00:02:15,250
Besides, I'm
getting really hungry.

11
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:16,791
Well I'm not worried...

12
00:02:16,875 --> 00:02:18,333
This is supposed
to show us the path

13
00:02:18,416 --> 00:02:20,625
we need to take for
world destruction.

14
00:02:20,708 --> 00:02:24,041
Really? It glows and it
acts like a compass too?

15
00:02:24,125 --> 00:02:25,458
Well, unless it
can make us some food

16
00:02:25,541 --> 00:02:28,083
we're gonna die before we get
a chance to end the world.

17
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:29,416
Real helpful...

18
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,333
Oh... What do you think
the chances are that thing

19
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:33,333
comes with a hidden
can opener function?

20
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:34,708
Are you insane...?

21
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,708
The only thing it does
is destroy the world.

22
00:02:36,791 --> 00:02:38,708
That's it;
nothing else.

23
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:40,000
[KYRIE] But you know
what everyone says!

24
00:02:40,083 --> 00:02:41,250
More is better, right?!

25
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:43,541
[MORTE] Give it back
before you drop it!

26
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:47,250
[BEAR] How did I get
myself into this mess...?

27
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:48,833
I never would have
thought in a million years

28
00:02:48,916 --> 00:02:50,208
I would end up
with the likes of these

29
00:02:50,291 --> 00:02:53,000
World Destruction
Committee goof-offs...

30
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:56,875
'Bout time I did something
about that Destruct Code.

31
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:58,666
Uh... Hey, you guys...

32
00:02:58,750 --> 00:02:59,875
Canned food's great and all,

33
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,916
but can we open
this bottle first?

34
00:03:05,375 --> 00:03:07,916
[KYRIE] Oh no! Not
another sand octopus!

35
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,583
Or is it a sand whale?!

36
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:13,958
No, that's a World Salvation
Committee subarenine!

37
00:03:14,041 --> 00:03:15,583
Subarenine?

38
00:03:15,666 --> 00:03:16,875
[SUB CAPTAIN laughing]

39
00:03:16,958 --> 00:03:19,333
Lucky us!
We actually found them!

40
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:21,041
Fire!

41
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:22,708
[WSC SOLDIER A] But what
about the Destruct Code?

42
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:24,583
Our weapons can't hurt it.

43
00:03:24,666 --> 00:03:27,958
Very soon we will take it
from their cold dead hands.

44
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:30,083
[SUB CAPTAIN] Now
shut your mouth and fire!

45
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:36,333
They're shooting at us!

46
00:03:36,416 --> 00:03:39,416
Abandon ship... kuma!

47
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:46,625
Hm...?

48
00:03:59,416 --> 00:04:01,000
There's no sign
of their bodies

49
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:02,583
or the Destruct
Code, Captain.

50
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:05,041
Hm... They
must've jumped ship.

51
00:04:05,125 --> 00:04:06,625
[SUB CAPTAIN] But they
couldn't have gotten far.

52
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:09,333
Call for more reinforcements
and search the entire area.

53
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,708
And make it snappy!

54
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,166
[WSC SOLDIERS] Yes, sir!

55
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:24,250
♪

56
00:04:24,333 --> 00:04:27,166
[PRIEST] May we
bid our final farewell.

57
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:37,208
♪

58
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,958
Morte...

59
00:05:05,208 --> 00:05:06,583
[MAN] Are you awake?

60
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:11,000
Where am I?

61
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,291
You're on my sand ship.

62
00:05:12,375 --> 00:05:14,625
This guy here helped
us out back there.

63
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:16,458
You were just barely
clinging to a board

64
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:18,041
and floating in the
middle of the Sand Sea

65
00:05:18,125 --> 00:05:19,916
when I came across you.

66
00:05:21,041 --> 00:05:23,166
[MAN] Yeah... Had I
not found the three of you,

67
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:24,666
you'd probably be
all chewed up in the

68
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,750
belly of a sand snake
at the bottom of the sea.

69
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:29,583
Well thank you!

70
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:31,916
Wow. You're more
polite than I thought...

71
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,791
for a member of the
World Destruction Committee.

72
00:05:35,833 --> 00:05:37,250
[MAN] I saw this
posted at the harbor

73
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:39,208
I stopped at this morning.

74
00:05:42,625 --> 00:05:44,750
Wait a second, I'm
not who you think I am.

75
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:47,000
Yeah, same goes
for me, kuma.

76
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:49,833
[MAN] Easy. There's no
need to get all worked up.

77
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:51,708
I'm not your enemy.

78
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:53,708
I'm Agan and I'm a smuggler.

79
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:56,000
If you got money, I'll
carry anything you want.

80
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,916
And that does not
exclude outlaws who are

81
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,916
trying to destroy the world...

82
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,500
How much... you got?

83
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:04,375
Are you trying
to threaten us?

84
00:06:04,458 --> 00:06:06,000
It'd be in your best interest

85
00:06:06,083 --> 00:06:07,791
to remember who we work for.

86
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:10,250
Wait... She's
speaking for herself.

87
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,583
You're still holding
that? Give it back.

88
00:06:13,458 --> 00:06:15,875
So is that really
the Destruct Code?

89
00:06:17,291 --> 00:06:20,708
[AGAN] I used to hear stories
about it when I was a kid.

90
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:23,541
The legend of an all powerful
secret hidden treasure...

91
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:26,625
The Destruct Code
that will end the world.

92
00:06:26,708 --> 00:06:29,500
[AGAN] I think the idea that
it's is hidden is only a myth...

93
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:31,833
Some say that it lies
at the bottom of the sea,

94
00:06:31,916 --> 00:06:34,041
while others claim
it's buried under glaciers

95
00:06:34,125 --> 00:06:37,208
in the winter continent, but
I don't believe any of that.

96
00:06:37,291 --> 00:06:39,125
And if that thing is
the real Destruct Code,

97
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:40,416
you guys are
sitting on the most

98
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,666
sought-after
treasures ever known.

99
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:45,166
Don't touch it! And
of course it's real.

100
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,791
Well... all she does is talk
about destroying the world

101
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:50,166
when in reality she doesn't
even know how to work it.

102
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,666
That's enough
out of you.

103
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,208
Oh... Okay...

104
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:54,750
Hold on, if you don't
know how to use it

105
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:57,083
then how can you be
certain it's genuine?

106
00:06:57,166 --> 00:06:58,875
The person who
had it before me...

107
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:00,625
would never lie to me.

108
00:07:10,583 --> 00:07:13,541
Fine... That's cool...
I believe you...

109
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:16,041
Now if you just hand over
the Destruct Code to me...

110
00:07:16,125 --> 00:07:18,958
I'll take you and your friends
anywhere you would like to go.

111
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:21,458
Oh please, you know I
can't give it to you.

112
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:23,541
Fine, cash
will work too.

113
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:26,250
This is all we
have for right now.

114
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,791
Wow, that's not much...

115
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:29,208
The only thing
you can buy from me

116
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:30,875
is this can
of sand whale.

117
00:07:30,958 --> 00:07:32,541
That's it, kuma!

118
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:35,083
It's time I step in
and do something, kuma!

119
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,416
Hello...?
Who said that?

120
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,208
I said it...! You can
talk to me now, kuma!

121
00:07:41,291 --> 00:07:43,916
What's up with this bear?
It knows how to talk?

122
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,416
Don't call me
bear, kuma!

123
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:48,000
Why not? That
is what you are.

124
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:49,875
[BEAR] Idiot, kuma.

125
00:07:54,125 --> 00:07:55,291
That's more like it!

126
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:57,500
This should settle up
on the bill just fine...

127
00:07:57,583 --> 00:07:59,916
I'm delivering a shipment
to the pleasure ship Jifnil

128
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,708
anyway so it's no
sweat taking you guys.

129
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:12,791
♪

130
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:22,500
[KYRIE] What's a pleasure ship?

131
00:08:22,583 --> 00:08:24,083
[AGAN] It's just
what it sounds like.

132
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,333
It's just a regular ship,
but it offers anything

133
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:27,958
you consider
to be pleasure.

134
00:08:28,041 --> 00:08:30,375
Whatever that might
be. Illegal gambling,

135
00:08:30,458 --> 00:08:32,166
bars stocked with
beautiful women...

136
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:34,916
Even secret nightclubs that are
normally off limit to minors.

137
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,166
[AGAN] The ship
literally has everything.

138
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:49,000
[AGAN] Okay,
that's the last of it...

139
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:51,875
Or I guess technically you
guys are the last of it.

140
00:08:51,958 --> 00:08:53,375
Hurry up and get off.

141
00:08:53,458 --> 00:08:55,333
Say what? Not here!

142
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:57,291
For what you paid me
this is all you get...

143
00:08:57,375 --> 00:08:59,875
Looks like the rest of
your trip'll be on the Jifnil.

144
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:01,583
Don't try to screw us, kuma!

145
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:04,166
C'mon, there's no
need to be like that.

146
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,875
The Jifnil is an outlaw zone.

147
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:08,083
Beastmen,
humans, no one cares...

148
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:10,250
In fact, it's the
perfect place for a group of

149
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:12,000
fugitives to
hide from the law.

150
00:09:12,083 --> 00:09:14,166
So why don't you
enjoy yourselves?

151
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:17,333
Heh. Sounds like fun
to me. Come on... bear.

152
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:18,666
Kuma!

153
00:09:18,750 --> 00:09:20,375
[AGAN] You too. Get going man!

154
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:22,041
[KYRIE] Uh...!

155
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:29,833
[AGAN] See you around!
And if we ever meet again,

156
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:31,375
bring more money!

157
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:35,125
Trust me, you'll find me much
more accommodating that way!

158
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:49,166
♪

159
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:56,375
Well hi there,
little bear...

160
00:09:56,458 --> 00:09:58,500
How about a drink
with some pretty girls?

161
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:00,125
No thanks, kuma.

162
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,875
The last thing we need
is to hang out in some

163
00:10:01,958 --> 00:10:04,333
seedy club and get
in more trouble, kuma.

164
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:07,000
The smart thing to do is to lay
low and mind our own business

165
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:08,958
until this ship
pulls into port, kuma.

166
00:10:09,041 --> 00:10:10,916
Sure, that sounds good
to me. But would you

167
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:13,541
stop saying "kuma" at
the end of every sentence?

168
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,458
She's got a point. I
mean you actually sound

169
00:10:15,541 --> 00:10:17,041
pretty cool when
you don't say it.

170
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:18,708
That I cannot do, kuma.

171
00:10:18,791 --> 00:10:22,208
That word is a proud symbol
of my native tribe, kuma.

172
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:23,666
[BOTH] Hm...

173
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:35,000
Sorry 'bout that!

174
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:36,166
What's a little
girl like her

175
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,750
doing on a
pleasure ship?

176
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,208
Beats me.

177
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,500
[knock knock]

178
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:45,958
[SHIP CAPTAIN] Come in.

179
00:10:47,083 --> 00:10:49,291
Who in the
hell are you people?

180
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,666
[MAN] It's a
pleasure to meet you.

181
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:53,125
My name is Nadja
and we are with

182
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:54,791
the World Salvation
Committee...

183
00:10:54,875 --> 00:10:57,208
My partner's
name here is Lia.

184
00:10:57,291 --> 00:10:58,916
The rest of them are with us.

185
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,791
[SHIP CAPTAIN] And?
So what exactly is

186
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,166
the World Salvation
Committee doing on my ship?

187
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,125
Some members of the
World Destruction Committee

188
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:08,333
recently disappeared in a
region not far from your ship...

189
00:11:08,416 --> 00:11:11,333
And we have reason to believe
that they may be on board.

190
00:11:11,416 --> 00:11:14,708
If that's true we'd appreciate
you turning them over to us.

191
00:11:14,791 --> 00:11:16,500
No way.

192
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:17,958
[grunt]

193
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:20,791
Wait... Would you care
to elaborate Captain?

194
00:11:20,875 --> 00:11:24,166
I do not care about my
patrons status in society.

195
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,208
There is only one place
on this entire planet

196
00:11:26,291 --> 00:11:28,208
that is not under
the control of the law...

197
00:11:28,291 --> 00:11:31,208
and that place is right
here on my ship, the Jifnil.

198
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:33,916
So if you would like to
look around then be my guest,

199
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,041
but don't expect us to lift
a finger to help you, got it?

200
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:41,166
I understand... That
should work out just fine.

201
00:11:52,666 --> 00:12:00,625
[chatter]

202
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,708
Here's that can
of sand whale I had.

203
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:05,500
And here. I found a
bottle opener for ya.

204
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,291
Wait... Where's Morte?

205
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:12,083
I swear she was around
here just a minute ago.

206
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:13,583
Huh, kuma.

207
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:23,958
I don't think
you've lost even once.

208
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:26,708
You got that right...
Guess I'm a lucky girl...

209
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:29,458
There's no way I'd be
alive today without luck...

210
00:12:29,541 --> 00:12:32,250
I'd like to put it
all on black... Got it?

211
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:33,416
You're betting all of it?

212
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,000
[MORTE] Mhmmm.

213
00:12:41,666 --> 00:12:44,041
A ha... Well
look who it is.

214
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:47,708
Not quite yet, Lia.

215
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:49,416
Nadja why are
you stopping me?

216
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,791
When in Rome, do
as the Romans do...

217
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:53,708
Since we're on this ship,
why don't we do things

218
00:12:53,791 --> 00:12:56,250
the way they would
prefer to do them?

219
00:12:56,333 --> 00:12:57,791
[sigh]

220
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:05,125
There's no sense in
looking for her, kuma...

221
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:07,041
After all, it's
not like I hold

222
00:13:07,125 --> 00:13:08,833
any allegiance
to her, kuma.

223
00:13:08,916 --> 00:13:10,291
But the three of us
have come such a long

224
00:13:10,375 --> 00:13:11,916
way together. And
what if something

225
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,833
bad has happened to her?

226
00:13:13,916 --> 00:13:14,833
Hold on...

227
00:13:14,916 --> 00:13:16,583
Do you have a
crush on Morte, kuma?

228
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,666
Huh...? Why
would you say that?

229
00:13:18,750 --> 00:13:20,250
Oh, nevermind, kuma...

230
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,791
My point is there's
no reason for us

231
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:23,833
to stay involved
with her anymore, kuma.

232
00:13:23,916 --> 00:13:25,541
But we're on a casino
ship, she could be

233
00:13:25,625 --> 00:13:27,333
getting ripped
off as we speak!

234
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:29,416
I don't see her as the kind
of girl to take a fleecing

235
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:31,083
lying down, if you
know what I mean...

236
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:33,625
She's one of the luckiest
girls I've seen, kuma.

237
00:13:33,708 --> 00:13:35,250
I guess...

238
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:40,583
Seems I underestimated you.

239
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:47,291
Well now... it would
certainly appear as though

240
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:49,833
the goddesses of good
fortune from around the world

241
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:51,833
have surrounded
you this evening.

242
00:13:53,708 --> 00:13:55,833
I was hoping... you
would be interested in

243
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:57,750
playing a game
of cards with me.

244
00:14:00,208 --> 00:14:01,833
Hmph.

245
00:14:01,916 --> 00:14:04,416
[BEAR] There are
two types of women, kuma.

246
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,583
Women who can take
care of themselves...

247
00:14:06,666 --> 00:14:08,125
and women who can't.

248
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:11,041
Morte is the type who can
get by on her own, kuma.

249
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:12,333
You're saying
just because she can

250
00:14:12,416 --> 00:14:14,833
take care of herself
means we can't help her?

251
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:16,500
Mister Hero.

252
00:14:16,583 --> 00:14:18,541
Hero's got places to be...

253
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,375
There's always gonna
be plenty of other people

254
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:22,791
in need of our
assistance, kuma.

255
00:14:25,208 --> 00:14:26,208
Wait, her again?

256
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:27,916
A girl like her's
exactly the type

257
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,291
to need my help, kuma...

258
00:14:29,375 --> 00:14:30,958
Find a way to get
her attention, kuma.

259
00:14:31,041 --> 00:14:33,208
Me...? What
for...? You can.

260
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:35,500
Just do it
already, kuma!

261
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:39,708
[KYRIE] Excuse me.
Is everything alright?

262
00:14:39,791 --> 00:14:41,166
This isn't the best
place for a young girl

263
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:43,250
to be walking
around by herself.

264
00:14:45,583 --> 00:14:47,708
Get lost...
Leave me alone...

265
00:14:47,791 --> 00:14:50,250
What I'm doing here is
none of your business.

266
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:51,708
Hey Toppy, I'm
starting to think this is

267
00:14:51,791 --> 00:14:53,541
one of those girls like Morte.

268
00:14:53,625 --> 00:14:54,666
Wait, kuma!

269
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:55,875
If there's
something going on

270
00:14:55,958 --> 00:14:57,416
then you can tell us, kuma...

271
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,000
You never know, we may
be able to help you out.

272
00:15:00,083 --> 00:15:01,500
What's with this bear?

273
00:15:01,583 --> 00:15:03,000
Don't call
me bear, kuma!

274
00:15:03,083 --> 00:15:04,375
Woah... easy...

275
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:07,208
Maybe she's just looking
for someone she knows, huh?

276
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:10,458
I came here to bring
my father back.

277
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:12,041
He's spends all
his time on this ship

278
00:15:12,125 --> 00:15:13,916
feeding his
gambling addiction.

279
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,041
But he racked
up a ton of debt

280
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:18,000
and now they're
holding him hostage.

281
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:20,166
That's too bad.

282
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:23,416
It serves him right if
I may say so myself.

283
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:26,083
If you really wanna help
then give me some money...

284
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:28,458
It could go a long
way towards saving him.

285
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:29,916
We don't have
any money, kuma.

286
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:31,708
Then you're
useless to me.

287
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:34,416
Hey, wait!

288
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:40,291
Oh oh!

289
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:41,750
[TOPPY] Kuma!

290
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:44,125
Mmm...

291
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:55,458
Now then...
What's your move?

292
00:15:55,541 --> 00:15:56,750
I'll stand.

293
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,208
Excellent.

294
00:16:00,291 --> 00:16:02,416
[crowd gasps]

295
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:07,750
[crowd chatter]

296
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:13,750
[heavy exhale]

297
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:16,166
Unlike your roulette,
card games require

298
00:16:16,250 --> 00:16:19,791
cool-headed decision making
as well as careful analysis.

299
00:16:19,875 --> 00:16:21,875
You can't win on luck alone.

300
00:16:21,958 --> 00:16:24,208
It's necessary to use this too.

301
00:16:24,291 --> 00:16:26,958
Are you suggesting I'm
incapable of using my brain?!

302
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:31,166
I said no such thing.
Shall we go on... my lady?

303
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:32,500
You got that right!

304
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:35,458
Watch, I'm gonna win it
all back with this hand.

305
00:16:35,541 --> 00:16:38,958
That is quite a wager.
Are you sure about this?

306
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,041
It seems the
goddesses of good fortune

307
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:52,500
have decided to
come over to my side.

308
00:16:53,666 --> 00:16:55,666
[crowd cheer]

309
00:16:56,666 --> 00:16:59,125
Now all of this
belongs to me.

310
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:04,666
So tell me, would
you be interested

311
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:07,250
in trying to win this
back with one last hand?

312
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:08,458
[MORTE] You cleaned me out.

313
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,333
I don't even have
a coin to my name.

314
00:17:10,416 --> 00:17:12,041
In that case,
maybe you could put up

315
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,083
something else as collateral.

316
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:15,666
Say... Oh I don't know,

317
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,916
perhaps something
like the Destruct Code...?

318
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,875
Miss Morte Urshela.

319
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,958
If you win, this
gigantic stack of chips

320
00:17:23,041 --> 00:17:24,208
will be all yours...

321
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:25,333
But if you were to lose,

322
00:17:25,416 --> 00:17:27,666
the Destruct Code
would belong to me.

323
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,583
This is taking too long...!

324
00:17:30,666 --> 00:17:32,750
I don't understand why we
have to pussy-foot around

325
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:34,166
when we could just
force her to give it over

326
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:35,875
and be done with it.

327
00:17:35,958 --> 00:17:37,541
That is quite
an offer...

328
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:40,166
I'm always up for a
challenge, so I accept.

329
00:17:40,250 --> 00:17:41,833
Music to my ears.

330
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:46,500
[MORTE] What the--?

331
00:17:46,583 --> 00:17:49,291
Is there a problem...?
Getting cold feet?

332
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:54,000
You think I'd give up
that easily...? Let's play.

333
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,625
[GIRL] Dad?! Dad?!

334
00:18:07,416 --> 00:18:09,583
[GIRL] Where's my father?
I want him back!

335
00:18:09,666 --> 00:18:11,708
[SHIP CAPTAIN laughs]

336
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:14,125
What a sassy
little thing you are...

337
00:18:14,208 --> 00:18:15,625
Well I don't mind
giving him back to you

338
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:18,083
but he owes me
a very large debt.

339
00:18:18,166 --> 00:18:20,375
[SHIP CAPTAIN] Do you have that
kind of money, little girl?

340
00:18:20,458 --> 00:18:22,958
No money, but I do
have something else.

341
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:25,875
[GIRL] It's a
priceless treasure with

342
00:18:25,958 --> 00:18:27,750
the power to
destroy the world...

343
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,666
It's the Destruct Code!

344
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:32,583
Hey...! That's mine!
Where'd you get that...?!

345
00:18:32,666 --> 00:18:34,666
[MORTE] Hand it
over you little thief!

346
00:18:37,666 --> 00:18:40,166
[gasp] You bet
with a can of fish?!

347
00:18:40,250 --> 00:18:48,875
♪

348
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:50,666
Not bad for a kid.

349
00:18:59,375 --> 00:19:01,333
Oh, look...
It's sand whale!

350
00:19:01,416 --> 00:19:02,833
[click, click]

351
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:08,333
See, I knew we
should have just taken it

352
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:10,208
from her in the first place.

353
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:17,916
Now get over here,
you little brat!

354
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,458
There's nowhere to run.

355
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,750
Now hand over
the Destruct Code.

356
00:19:32,916 --> 00:19:42,875
♪

357
00:19:45,291 --> 00:19:46,708
[LIA growls]

358
00:19:46,791 --> 00:19:48,666
Uh, huh...? Ahhh!

359
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:50,500
[growls]

360
00:19:50,583 --> 00:19:52,041
Uh...

361
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:57,250
Uh-hu...

362
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:02,708
[exhale]

363
00:20:03,166 --> 00:20:04,541
Kyrie!

364
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:06,000
Lia!

365
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:11,208
[power yell]

366
00:20:12,208 --> 00:20:16,416
[crowd panicking]

367
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:21,666
[distant yelling]

368
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:22,666
[MAN] Stop them!

369
00:20:22,750 --> 00:20:25,166
[TOPPY] We gotta go now, kuma!

370
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:26,458
Come on. Hop in.

371
00:20:26,541 --> 00:20:28,375
Uh... Mm-mmm.

372
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:31,833
I can't go with you. I have
to save my father first.

373
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:33,875
You can come back
and save him later.

374
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:36,375
Right now we all just
need to get to safety.

375
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:37,625
I'm not
scared of them.

376
00:20:37,708 --> 00:20:38,916
Besides, they're
not after me,

377
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,583
they're after the World
Destruction Committee,

378
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:42,083
which is you guys.

379
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:43,166
You know what?
She's right.

380
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:44,666
We gotta go. Now!

381
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:46,125
Wait, hold on.

382
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:51,375
That can should fetch you
at least one silver coin.

383
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:53,666
I'm sorry but I can't
give you the Destruct Code.

384
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,083
But you can use
that as seed money

385
00:20:55,166 --> 00:20:56,875
to get your dad out of here.

386
00:20:58,291 --> 00:20:59,916
Thanks a lot.

387
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:12,708
[NADJA] We let them
slip through our fingers.

388
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:14,916
It was... my fault.

389
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,583
World Destruction...

390
00:21:17,541 --> 00:21:19,625
Why do they
want destruction?

391
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:23,083
They sure have
piqued my curiousity.

392
00:21:33,916 --> 00:21:35,833
[BOTH heavy exhale]

393
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:38,291
Later guys. I'm
gonna head out now.

394
00:21:38,375 --> 00:21:40,875
Sorry to get you two
mixed up in all this mess.

395
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:42,333
[BOTH] Huh...?

396
00:21:43,916 --> 00:21:46,083
Uh... Hey, where
are you going...?!

397
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:47,208
Is that how it is?

398
00:21:47,291 --> 00:21:49,166
You're just gonna
leave us stranded here?

399
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:51,375
What? You
wanna come with me?

400
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:53,583
Uh... That's not
exactly what I meant...

401
00:21:53,666 --> 00:21:57,208
It's just Toppy and I are
fugitives now, and you know...

402
00:21:57,291 --> 00:22:00,125
Well if you want to tag
along I won't stop you.

403
00:22:01,541 --> 00:22:03,125
So... I have an idea.

404
00:22:03,208 --> 00:22:04,875
Why don't we forget
all this world destruction

405
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:06,875
nonsense and
help people instead...?

406
00:22:06,958 --> 00:22:08,916
I mean that really seems
to be the way it's going.

407
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,375
We end up helping
someone in the end anyway.

408
00:22:11,458 --> 00:22:13,875
Nice idea, but
the way this world is,

409
00:22:13,958 --> 00:22:17,125
we'd be helping people
by destroying it for them.

410
00:22:17,208 --> 00:22:19,250
What are you
gonna do, Toppy?

411
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:20,958
You guys'll probably
need me, so I guess

412
00:22:21,041 --> 00:22:23,000
I'll stick around
for now, kuma.

413
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:05,750
[KYRIE] I don't know how this
happened, but we got captured!

414
00:24:05,833 --> 00:24:08,000
Soon enough we found
ourselves behind bars

415
00:24:08,083 --> 00:24:11,208
in a notorious prison
run by a pack of wolves!

416
00:24:11,291 --> 00:24:12,916
Now we have to
find a way to escape

417
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,375
before those two from the World
Salvation Committee show up.

418
00:24:16,458 --> 00:24:18,625
Next time on
Sands of Destruction,

419
00:24:18,708 --> 00:24:20,958
"There are Two
Kinds of Beastmen."

420
00:24:21,041 --> 00:24:22,708
Hey, where's Toppy?

421
00:24:22,791 --> 00:24:25,375
[MORTE] He's
over there... sulking.

422
00:24:25,458 --> 00:24:27,541
[TOPPY] A hero in prison...?

423
00:24:27,625 --> 00:24:30,791
What's the world
coming to... kuma?

